PN,41601
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1775139065
OL,3,CFirefighters vote in favour of strikes
OL,4,Cover planned cuts to fire service
OL,6,FFirefighters in Oxfordshire have
OL,7,Fbacked potential strike action over
OL,8,Fproposed cuts to the county's fire and
OL,9,Frescue service.
OL,11,FThe Fire Brigades Union said more than
OL,12,Ftwo thirds of firefighters - 94% of
OL,13,Ffirefighters in a turnout of 71% voted
OL,14,F"yes".
OL,16,FThe ballot is against plans put
OL,17,Fforward by Oxfordshire County Council
OL,18,F- which could see the closure of three
OL,19,Fon-call fire stations in Woodstock,
OL,20,FEynsham and Henley.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1775139065
OL,3,CFirefighters vote in favour of strikes
OL,4,Cover planned cuts to fire service
OL,6,FIt could also see fire engines move
OL,7,Ffrom Rewley Road and Kidlington
OL,8,Fstations, to a new one north of Oxford.
OL,10,FThe FBU said a minimum of 42
OL,11,Ffirefighters also face losing their
OL,12,Fjobs under the proposals.
OL,14,FFBU General Secretary Steve Wright
OL,15,Fsaid: "The result of this consultative
OL,16,Fballot could not be clearer. If
OL,17,FOxfordshire County Council don't move
OL,18,Fquickly to scrap the proposed cuts,
OL,19,Fthen the likelihood of strike action
OL,20,Fin the fire and rescue service moves
OL,21,Fever closer.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1775139065
OL,3,CFirefighters vote in favour of strikes
OL,4,Cover planned cuts to fire service
OL,6,F"The proposals we are facing will put
OL,7,Fpublic safety, firefighter safety and
OL,8,Four communities at risk. This is
OL,9,Fsimply not something we can stand by
OL,10,Fand let happen. We have written to
OL,11,Fthose responsible for proposing these
OL,12,Fcuts on this much valued public
OL,13,Fservice to withdraw these proposals.
OL,15,F"There can be no price put on the
OL,16,Fsafety of firefighters and the public
OL,17,Fwe serve, and we will do all we can to
OL,18,Fstop these cuts from happening. If
OL,19,Fthat means moving to a formal ballot
OL,20,Ffor strike action then that is what we
OL,21,Fwill do.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1775139065
OL,3,CFirefighters vote in favour of strikes
OL,4,Cover planned cuts to fire service
OL,6,F"It is not too late for those in
OL,7,Fauthority to step back from the edge
OL,8,Fand do what is right for the fire and
OL,9,Frescue service and for the public.
OL,11,F"As well as our message to Oxfordshire
OL,12,FCounty Council, we will take this
OL,13,Fargument to Government, to the Fire
OL,14,FMinister and to the Prime Minister.
OL,16,F"They need to be aware of the real
OL,17,Fdamage these cuts will have when it
OL,18,Fcomes to the safety of the public we
OL,19,Fserve."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1775139065
OL,3,CFirefighters vote in favour of strikes
OL,4,Cover planned cuts to fire service
OL,6,FJohnny Shuker, Oxfordshire Brigade
OL,7,FSecretary said: "Oxfordshire
OL,8,Ffirefighters are ready to strike this
OL,9,Fsummer if the cuts to our service are
OL,10,Fnot abandoned.
OL,12,F"More wildfires and extreme weather
OL,13,Fevents are expected during the summer
OL,14,Fmonths. By refusing to shelve these
OL,15,Fcuts, the county council is leaving
OL,16,Ffirefighters with no choice but to go
OL,17,Fon strike during that time.
OL,19,F"It is playing fast and loose with
OL,20,Fpublic safety and that of firefighters
OL,21,Fby pressing ahead with these cutbacks."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1775139065
OL,3,CFirefighters vote in favour of strikes
OL,4,Cover planned cuts to fire service
OL,6,FIn a statement Oxfordshire Chief Fire
OL,7,FOfficer Rob MacDougall said: "We are
OL,8,Faware of the Fire Brigades Union's
OL,9,F(FBU) nonstatutory ballot.
OL,11,F"This does not mean industrial action
OL,12,Fat this stage. We remain committed to
OL,13,Fopen engagement with the FBU and our
OL,14,Fcolleagues as discussions continue.
OL,16,F"Oxfordshire County Council Fire and
OL,17,FRescue Service is continuing to
OL,18,Fanalyse the feedback received through
OL,19,Four public consultation. We will
OL,20,Fprovide a formal response to our
OL,21,Fcommunities in April.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
